description: Was backpacking at Piute Lake in the Eastern Sierras awhile back and caught this trout throwing a small silver spoon. Also caught a couple rainbows at the same spot. There is another smaller glacier lake, Emerson lake which is about a 200 foot cross country climb above Piute to the south. We hiked up there one afternoon, that lake was choked with smaller hungry brook trout was catching them on just about every cast I made.
